Chelsea Flower Show 'like a drug', says Joanna Lumley
Actress Joanna Lumley, speaking to the Telegraph's Ed Cumming, reveals what inspiration she will be taking back to her own garden from this year's Chelsea Flower Show. 4:04PM BST 20 May 2013
Comments
Speaking on the first day of Chelsea Flower Show, the actress said "every year it thrills me more and more."
Lending a hand on Marks and Spencer's stall, the Absolutely Fabulous star said she often took inspiration home to her own London garden.
"Everywhere you go you just get inspired, you get overawed with the beauty." "The whole thing is like fairy land," she added.
