Why I love the great British pub - even when sober
Dry January: Tara Gladden is still supporting her local during her month off the grog. And yet, despite being sober, she still managed to pick a fight... British pubs are totally unique. By Tara Gladden
12:42PM GMT 11 Jan 2013
She’s holding a glass of wine. I’m holding a glass of water.
‘So how’s it all going? You know, the whole not-drinking thing?’ She cocks her head, smiles and looks expectantly at me. “Slowly.”
“But it’s…”
“Boring. Yeah, really boring.”
